      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Concept ACK. I'm not aware of any major projects still on Py2 and intending to stay there. AFAIK, just about everything that's still Py2 is due to legacy and/or manpower issues. Here's how I'd like to see things handled.\r\n\r\n- Make the decision to go Py3-only.\r\n- Add something in release notes for the next major version (0.16 or 0.17, I assume) indicating that Py2 will no longer be usable in the following version.\r\n- Make the changes, and force any config/make materials reliant on Python to ensure that Py3 is present.",
      "created_at" : "2017-12-12T23:10:23Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/11881#issuecomment-351225803",
